docs.abstract: The Fed’s newfound patience on raising interest rates is just what President Trump wanted. Its explanation, however, is unlikely to please him.
docs.snippet: The Fed’s newfound patience on raising interest rates is just what President Trump wanted. Its explanation, however, is unlikely to please him.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Trump in 2018 repeatedly urged the Federal Reserve to stop raising interest rates, warning that its “crazy” policies were jeopardizing the economic expansion.

headline.main: Trump’s Policies, Not His Insults, Contributed to the Fed’s Shift
headline.print_headline: Fed Leaves Rates Alone, But Not to Pacify Trump

docs.abstract: The investment bank’s board adopted a provision to claw back, or reduce, some of the pay packages they received last year, depending on the outcome of a federal inquiry into a fraud in Malaysia.
docs.snippet: The investment bank’s board adopted a provision to claw back, or reduce, some of the pay packages they received last year, depending on the outcome of a federal inquiry into a fraud in Malaysia.
docs.lead_paragraph: The fallout for Goldman Sachs from a scandal tied to a Malaysian investment fund could mean lower pay for several senior executives at the Wall Street bank, including the chief executive, David Solomon, and his predecessor, Lloyd Blankfein.

headline.main: Goldman Sachs Suggests Current and Former Executives Could Lose Money Over 1MDB
headline.print_headline: Goldman Executives’ Pay  May Be Cut Over Scandal

docs.abstract: A House committee grilled Sundar Pichai, the chief executive of Google, about a variety of issues, including worries about personal data and complaints about search results.
docs.snippet: A House committee grilled Sundar Pichai, the chief executive of Google, about a variety of issues, including worries about personal data and complaints about search results.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Google’s chief executive, in perhaps the most public display of lawmakers’ unease with his company’s influence, was grilled on Tuesday about everything from search result bias and the data Google collects about its users to plans for a censored service in China.

headline.main: Google’s Pichai Faces Privacy and Bias Questions in Congress
headline.print_headline: House Sees Trust Gap As It Grills Google Chief

docs.abstract: If recent increases are any indication, chances are your next iDevice will cost even more. We analyzed how prices have shot up and offer ways to buy for less.
docs.snippet: If recent increases are any indication, chances are your next iDevice will cost even more. We analyzed how prices have shot up and offer ways to buy for less.

docs.abstract: A teenager in Arizona discovered the flaw, which allows eavesdropping, on Jan. 19, and his mother contacted Apple the next day. But the company was slow to reply.
docs.snippet: A teenager in Arizona discovered the flaw, which allows eavesdropping, on Jan. 19, and his mother contacted Apple the next day. But the company was slow to reply.
docs.lead_paragraph: SAN FRANCISCO — On Jan. 19, Grant Thompson, a 14-year-old in Arizona, made an unexpected discovery: Using FaceTime, Apple’s video chatting software, he could eavesdrop on his friend’s phone before his friend had even answered the call.

headline.main: Apple Was Slow to Act on FaceTime Bug That Allows Spying on iPhones
headline.print_headline: Warned That iPhone App Could Snoop, Apple Acted Slowly

keywords.name: subject
keywords.value: Wiretapping and Other Eavesdropping Devices and Methods

docs.abstract: Pacific Gas and Electric has filed for Chapter 11 bankruptcy protection. The state’s wildfires are at the heart of its insolvency.
docs.snippet: Pacific Gas and Electric has filed for Chapter 11 bankruptcy protection. The state’s wildfires are at the heart of its insolvency.
docs.lead_paragraph: Pacific Gas and Electric, California’s largest utility, serving more than 16 million people, filed for bankruptcy protection on Tuesday because it is facing tens of billions of dollars in liability for wildfires. The company’s equipment could be responsible for causing wildfires that killed dozens of people, destroyed thousands of homes and resulted in billions of dollars in damage over the past few years.

headline.main: California’s Largest Utility Says It Is Bankrupt. Here’s What You Need to Know.

docs.abstract: The e-commerce giant posted numbers that pale in comparison to earlier surging figures, a sign of the country’s economic slowdown.
docs.snippet: The e-commerce giant posted numbers that pale in comparison to earlier surging figures, a sign of the country’s economic slowdown.
docs.lead_paragraph: SHANGHAI — Alibaba became one of the world’s biggest internet companies thanks to the growing wealth and online shopping habits of Chinese consumers. Now, as China’s economy slows, it has become a symbol of their new sense of caution.

headline.main: Alibaba, an Icon of China’s Growth, Now Reflects Its Slowdown
headline.print_headline: Alibaba’s Earnings Reflect China’s Cooling Economy

docs.abstract: Despite a painful year of scandals, the social network reported Wednesday that it continued to grow in the fourth quarter.
docs.snippet: Despite a painful year of scandals, the social network reported Wednesday that it continued to grow in the fourth quarter.
docs.lead_paragraph: SAN FRANCISCO — Facebook’s worst year ever was its best year ever when it came to its business.

headline.main: Facebook’s Profits and Revenue Climb as It Gains More Users
headline.print_headline: Facebook Wrings Record Profit Out of Rough Year

docs.abstract: Airlines’ most valuable customers — the ones who fly and spend the most — get lots of perks. For everyone else, it has become more complicated to qualify.
docs.snippet: Airlines’ most valuable customers — the ones who fly and spend the most — get lots of perks. For everyone else, it has become more complicated to qualify.
docs.lead_paragraph: The airlines’ most valuable customers, those who fly most often and spend the most money, receive the sorts of benefits that most travelers can only salivate over — lounge access, free checked luggage, free upgrades, free itinerary changes.

headline.main: These Days, ‘You Practically Need a Ph.D.’ to Figure Out Frequent-Flier Status
